  "prompt": "The Last Man on Earth (TV series): Where did all the dead bodies go on The Last Man on Earth?",
  "response": "In \"The Last Man on Earth,\" the series implies that many of the dead bodies of those who succumbed to the virus that wiped out most of humanity were either left where they died or disposed of in various ways. The show occasionally addresses the aftermath of the pandemic through dialogue and character interactions but does not provide explicit details or visuals of the bodies. It suggests that the characters, primarily Phil Miller and others he encounters, need to navigate a world where they are largely alone, with few reminders of the people who once populated it. The show focuses more on the implications of isolation and survival rather than on the graphic realities of death in the world they inhabit.",
